<Author>yamanote
<Content>Excellent Hotel, Ritz Carlton Experience Stayed 4 nights at the RC Dallas on a business trip. The hotel was within 10 minutes walking distance to the major office towers in downtown Dallas. The walk is ok on a nice day.Check in is was very efficient. The front entrance is guarded by door men and valets, so lots of attention is given to arriving guests. The lobby is striking with a large flower and candle display in the center of the floor. A polite bell man showed me to my room, giving an explanation of the hotel and filling the room ice bucket upon arrival. I requested a razor from the bell man (I forgot mine) but it was never delivered - apparently forgotten. In a pinch I was able to buy one later in the hotel gift shop for $2.50. The room was very nice. The bed is very fluffy with an assortment of pillows on hand - hard, soft, feather, non feather. A large flat screen TV and DVD player was provided, along with a fully stocked in room bar (not utilized).The bathroom was spacious, with both a bathtub and shower provided. Hot water was very slow in the shower, taking up to 5 minutes to come out. Soap and amenities are Bulgari, a nice touch but too perfumed for me.In room internet was very fast, true broadband speed. My slingbox test showed about 500 kbps.Room service was very good. The menu is not too extensive and heavy on comfort foods. Both the salad and hamburger menu take up one page each in the menu book. The menu is sufficient for most business and leisure travelers. The bar off the lobby is a great design and very attractive. In the early evening it can get crowded and customers spill out into the lobby. Drinks can be expensive - $15 for a cocktail.The restaurant is similarly well designed. Went for breakfast one morning, but slow service caused me to abandon my table prior to ordering. After 15 minutes and one request my order was not taken and I timed out. Breakfast prices expensive - coffee is $6, bagels over $10. The fitness center is well equiped and perfect for a business traveler.One comment on DFW airport- access to the city is horrible. The choices are shared ride or taxi. Taxi is about $50 to the hotel. Shared ride can take over an hour. Public transportation is basically unavailable. Aside from availability, travel to the airport is fairly quick, about 30 min direct if there is no traffic. Overall I found the Ritz Carlton Dallas to be a very high quality hotel and I would stay there again on future visits to Dallas. 
